comment.text:
Von's has long been on my list of places to try for a sit-down dinner in Seattle! I ate here in a group of seven on a Friday night (with a reservation) and the service was solid, quick, and friendly. The food was delicious, with much of the menu circling around sourdough in various forms.

We got a few sourdough pastas, which were huge and filling. Von's used a unique, twisted pasta shape for all pastas, which presents beautifully on a plate. These are definitely heavy, more oily dishes, so I'd not recommend ordering a pasta if you plan to be active afterwards.

My favorite dish was the sourdough pizza. The crust was soft but not too thick, and there were ample toppings. It was just crispy enough and served fresh. The salad was a good balance to all the carbs, though in the future, I'd probably add chicken or something more hearty to it.

comment.text:
We had the best server ever, Traci was great!
Loved the ambience of this restaurant and the drink options!
Def recommend the seafood stew!

I'm not usually a huge fan of American restaurants because the food is uninspiring and forgettable (you know, burgers, pasta, whatever) but Von's blew me away.

My partner and I ordered their salmon pasta, the balsamic pizza, and the clams. The pasta was by and large the star of the show. Something about that creamy, tangy sauce and the shape of the pasta picking all the sauce up + the succulent, somewhat fishy taste - literally chef's kiss. So delicious and decadent. The pizza was also good and I enjoyed dipping it in the pasta sauce and clam sauce, but not as unique. Clams were also tasty, a bit spicy and fun to eat, but definitely that pasta was the best. They were also kind enough to split it into two plates and the portion was very good.

They are open late, service is good, and it's definitely moody/dark. I really liked my time here and will be back the next time I'm in Seattle!

I love this place! I went with some friends on a busy Friday night before catching an improv show at Pike Place. It was packed, but we had made a reservation for our party of 8 and they were very accommodating. We got seated in the back room immediately, and our server for the night was friendly, funny, and made great food recommendations.

I ordered an espresso martini and the tellicherry chicken and smoked gouda pasta. I loved the pasta shape! It was cooked well and held up in the sauce. I was worried it'd be too cheesy, but it definitely wasn't and the amount of black pepper they added was truly *chef's kiss*. It was also a big portion, and I had enough to take home for a second meal. For such a large party, our food came out pretty quickly and I was overall very pleasantly surprised by the service.

comment.text:
This was a great place to get a last-minute dinner with friends. We were all visiting town for a wedding and found Von's to be a really convenient location for us. It's right near the Pike's Place Market and is walkable to that area. The location is great - right near the water with lots of big windows and natural lighting. They also have an open kitchen and tons of bar seating, so the ambiance is fun and upbeat. Our favorite was the wheel they would spin that determines which alcohol is on discount.

Our server was attentive and made sure we could hear him clearly as the inside was a bit noisy. We ordered everything off the happy hour menu and it was a great deal. 2 beers, a margarita, two flatbreads, and the cod tacos. We ate everything! So tasty! I really loved the pizza - it was a bit big for me to eat alone so I brought the last piece home for a perfect late night snacks.

We didn't order these, but I want to give a shout-out to the fun cocktails on the menu. They are perfect for birthdays or special events as they are an event in and of themselves. We saw others ordering drinks with sparklers shooting out of them, or others with spun sugar that would dissolve with the drink poured table side. It was fun even just to watch!

comment.text:
Stopped by around 9pm on a Saturday (after a Mariner's game). Was seated after the waitress quickly prepped our table.

We opted for the Northwest King Salmon Pasta, Bolognese, and our waitress suggested the broccoli since we were browsing for a vegetable. The salmon pasta was amazing - creamy sauce and great pasta. Wish there was a bit more salmon (a few chunks here and there), but the flavor was great. The bolognese was good, with strips of pork belly scattered through the dish. However, both of us preferred the salmon pasta. Broccoli was surprisingly our favorite dish that evening - perfectly cooked with just the right amount of charring.

Our drinks were great as well, a bit strong upon the first sip, but after a bit of chatting and eating, the ice had melted to transform the drinks in the palatable beverages.

A bit pricey, but well worth. Hope to be back!

comment.text: 3rd time here and the first I've been disappointed. The meatballs are always amazing. Nothing to complain about there. Unfortunately the calamari was probably my the worst I've had. It is supposed to be Toragashi season served with a chili aioli. It was most certainly the blandest fried calamari I've had for something supposed to be seasoned. The aioli was weak at best. It needed more heat. The worst part: the calamari was like chewing rubber. They were so chewy and tough. I could have bought frozen and made them at home for a similar experience. Really not what I would expect from Von's. Lastly, our dod was served warm like it had sat for too long before being served. I like the food here usually. I hope the chef/sous chef does more QC on the calamari soon because it was really unacceptable to serve.

Von's is my partner and I's go-to when in the area and we love bringing family and friends here to experience it. The food, cocktails, and service are all incredible and we know that anyone we bring will find something to enjoy here. The prices are reasonable for the area and the quantity and quality of what is served. It consistently hits every time!

comment.text:
After 9:00pm on a Monday night, it can be challenging finding good food, in a nice ambience, with friendly service, in any city! Thankfully Vons's 1000 is open until midnight, even on a Monday! Wife and I arrived around 9:30pm, and were promptly seated and served by the friendly hostess and waitress. Â Ambience is elegant without being pretentious even with sports on the TVs, making it relaxed and casual as the same time. Kitchen closes at 11:45pm, but don't be that guy. Â 

$18 Charred Avocado Caesar, large...its huge! It was served on two separate plates, without us even having to ask! Now that's service! The unique and create lemon caesar dressing and avocado made this a sensational caesar salad! My 2nd favorite in the world!

$26 Quatre Viande (4 Meat) Pizza....Torrid Wurst, soppressata, lardons, pepperoni, whole milk mozzarella, grated parm...its basically their meat lovers pizza, and we did indeed LOVE it! Â Von's claim to fame is their unique sourdough crust, which adds extra flavor and creativity to an already fantastic pizza! Where else are you gonna find a sourdough pizza? Its shareable for two people, but if I was really really hungry I could've eaten the entire thing cause I'm a fatty! Â 

Von's 1000....worth eating before or after 9:00pm on a Monday night :)

comment.text:
We asked a friend for some recommendations of where to eat in Seattle, as we were visiting for a few days. Von's 1000 spirits was on her list and she had said "everyone loved what they ordered there". I'm happy to say we did too!

We ordered:

CHAMPAGNE MANGO MARGARITA -- this was delicious! Both my husband and I found it refreshing and not overly sweet. The tajin on the rim was a nice touch.

PORK CONFIT FRIES-- a little on the salty side but the fries were crisp and the pork was tender. With a glass of beer and my margarita to help balance out the saltiness, this was a good starter.

TELLICHERRY CHICKEN AND SMOKED GOUDA--this came highly recommended. I'm glad I took my friends advice and ordered this because it's one of the tastiest pasta dishes I've had. The sourdough pasta was unique and the sauce was not drowning it or overpowering the flavor. It was just right. This was a lot of food and can easily be shared.

SEATTLE STEW-- my husband said this dish reminded him of cioppino, I did too. They did a good job not over cooking the fish and the broth was fantastic.

The vibe here was very chill. I could see friends coming here to hang out and have a couple drinks. Our service was great, though the hostess could've been nicer and more welcoming. Overall, a great meal for our first night in Seattle.

Would definitely recommend this to anyone, for a date night, a casual hangout with friends, or a solo meal.

comment.text:
The family and I had dinner last night at Von's 1000 Spirits. It was a great way to wrap up our first and only day in Seattle before heading out on our Alaska cruise.

Our reservation was for 7:45. When we arrived there were several people waiting for a table. The hostess quickly seated us at a table near the front window.

Our server, Traci, arrived to take our order. We were a little overwhelmed by the menu but Traci went over the highlights for us. She has the menu memorized.

As tempting as the small bites menu was, we decided just to move on to mains. I ordered the Tellicherry Chicken and Smoked Gouda from the Sourdough pasta menu. It is one of Von's most popular dishes. Beautifully crafted pasta tossed in a garlic cream sauce with organic chicken and fresh cracked Tellicherry pepper. A very rich dish to say the least. The smokiness of the Gouda combined with the citrus notes from the Tellicherry were a party on my tastebuds. I added mushrooms for some extra texture. Kiddo ordered the Original Mac and 4 Cheeses with bacon added on fir texture and flavor. She loved it.

The Mrs. had Mary's Peppered Fried Chicken Sandwich. It was just ok and very messy to eat. The fries that came with it were cold.

My only complaints are that the food came out way too fast and arrived before our drinks did. Other than that, the service we received from Traci was great.

comment.text: First time in Seattle and was recommended by a friend to come try it. I'm not familiar with the area at all, so parking was difficult for me to find. I ended up parking at Pike's Place for ~$4 and walked about 10 minutes to the restaurant on a Tuesday night. Once inside, it had a nice atmosphere with friendly staff and very quick service. From the moment I stepped foot inside to leaving, I was there for only ~45 minutes (dined solo). I can see why many reviews said it's a great location for drinks, the bar had large selections of alcohol. Sadly, I had to drive so I drank a strawberry lemonade, which was refreshing and sour. The basil almond pesto pasta was pretty good! I could taste the pesto but it wasn't overwhelming, and the cherry tomatoes were like little flavor bombs with each bite. Portions were large for me, so I packed half of my meal to-go.

Von's 1000 spirits deserves more than 5 stars . The service was quick, super friendly, and tasty! The restaurant is located in a convenient area with cool spots worth checking nearby, depending on the time of day.

The eggplant hummus is an absolute must! I had the vegan pasta and my friend had a cheesy chicken pasta. I Â  can't wait to come back!
